>
> On further inspection the crank pulley itself had rust.
where the fan belt
> rides.  I figured this acts like sandpaper and wears the
belt down.   I had
> seen this before on several buses, and one that was on a
road trip last summer
> (not mine) had been 'going through fan belts'... well i
suggested sanding the
> pulley down, but the engine was already making a bad noise
and didn't get them
> home  :(
>
Lucky it was just a rusty pulley.

If a bus is eating fan belts and also making odd noises,
especially when engaging/disengaging the clutch, then it
very likely has a loose flywheel.

If it runs loose for any length of time it destroys the
crankshaft.

BTDT.

